HEADWORD: hemolysis
<hw>hemolysis</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>The lysis of erythrocytes with the
release of hemoglobin; the breaking apart of red blood cells in the
blood.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> haemolysis, hematolysis, haematolysis.</syn>⟦br⟧
